# Phase 7: ModLoader Installer (Fabric)

## Goal
Enable the launcher to automatically install the Fabric Modloader when importing a Modpack or upon user request.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This phase focuses on **Fabric** first, as it's the primary loader for Modrinth modpacks. NeoForge/Forge support will be added in a subsequent update due to its higher complexity (installers/processors).

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Logic
#### [NEW] [ModLoaderService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModLoaderService.cs)
-   **Purpose**: Handle metadata fetching and installation for mod loaders.
-   **Methods**:
    -   `InstallFabricAsync(string mcVersion, string loaderVersion, string gamePath)`
    -   Fetches specific version JSON from `https://meta.fabricmc.net/v2/versions/loader/{game_version}/{loader_version}/profile/json`.
    -   Parses libraries and downloads them using [DownloadService](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Network/DownloadService.cs#25-39).
    -   Saves the version JSON to `.minecraft/versions/{version_id}/{version_id}.json`.

#### [MODIFY] [ModpackService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs)
-   Inject `ModLoaderService`.
-   In [ImportMrPackAsync](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs#20-123), detecting `fabric-loader` dependency:
    -   Call `ModLoaderService.InstallFabricAsync`.
    -   Update the modpack's `version.json` to inherit safely or just rely on the installed Fabric version if we make the pack a separate instance using that version.
    -   *Better approach*: The Modpack creates a specific version folder (e.g. `MyPack`). We should probably just install the Fabric libraries *into* this version's json or make `MyPack` inherit from the installed Fabric version.
    -   *Simpler for now*: Download Fabric JSON, rename id to `ModpackName`, save it in `versions/ModpackName/ModpackName.json`. This makes the modpack a standalone version with Fabric built-in.

### UI / Integration
-   Progress reporting in [ModpackService](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs#15-19) handles the loader installation steps.

## Verification Plan
### Automated / Manual Tests
1.  **Fabric Installation**:
    -   Import a Fabric-based Modpack.
    -   Verify `versions/{ModpackName}/{ModpackName}.json` contains Fabric libraries and main class.
    -   Verify Fabric libraries are downloaded to `libraries/`.
2.  **Launch Test**:
    -   Launch the imported modpack.
    -   Verify the game starts and Fabric is active (check title screen or log).
